    <string name="financial_tips_title">FAMILY FINANCIAL TIPS (2 CHILDREN)</string>
    <string name="tips_1_title">Use the Envelope Budgeting Rule</string>
    <string name="tips_1_desc">Divide income into family posts: 50% Basic Needs &amp; Milk, 20% Education/Courses, 20% Savings/Emergency Fund, and 10% Family Entertainment.</string>
    <string name="tips_2_title">Monthly Bulk Shopping</string>
    <string name="tips_2_desc">For routine needs of 2 children (such as detergent, soap, diapers, or rice), buy large bulk packages. This is 15-20% more efficient than weekly retail.</string>
    <string name="tips_3_title">Prioritize Double Emergency Funds</string>
    <string name="tips_3_desc">With two children, the risk of medical emergencies or sudden school needs doubles. Secure at least 6x monthly expenses in a separate account.</string>
    <string name="tips_4_title">Evaluate Weekly Micro-Leaks</string>
    <string name="tips_4_desc">Often the budget leaks in casual toys, food delivery, or weekend toy rentals. Strictly limit the \'Child Snack Budget\' per week.</string>

